================================================================================
GTK 3 (GIMP Toolkit)
================================================================================
License: LGPL-2.1-or-later
Website: https://gtk.org/
Source:  https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gtk
Full license: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gtk/-/blob/gtk-3-24/COPYING

GTK is a multi-platform toolkit for creating graphical user interfaces.
shellkeep uses GTK 3 for all UI elements including windows, dialogs,
menus, and the application framework (GtkApplication).

================================================================================
GLib
================================================================================
License: LGPL-2.1-or-later
Website: https://docs.gtk.org/glib/
Source:  https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/glib
Full license: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/glib/-/blob/main/COPYING

GLib provides core non-graphical functionality used by GTK and shellkeep,
including the main event loop (GMainLoop), threading (GTask), data
structures, file utilities, and D-Bus integration.

================================================================================
VTE (Virtual Terminal Emulator)
================================================================================
License: LGPL-2.1-or-later
Website: https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Terminal/VTE
Source:  https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/vte
Full license: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/vte/-/blob/master/COPYING.LGPL2

VTE is the terminal emulator widget library used by GNOME Terminal and
other GTK-based terminals. shellkeep uses libvte-2.91 for terminal
rendering, scrollback, input handling, and escape sequence processing.

================================================================================
libssh
================================================================================
License: LGPL-2.1-or-later
Website: https://www.libssh.org/
Source:  https://git.libssh.org/projects/libssh.git
Full license: https://git.libssh.org/projects/libssh.git/tree/COPYING

libssh is a C library implementing the SSH protocol. shellkeep uses
libssh >= 0.9.6 for all SSH connections, authentication, channel
management, and SFTP file operations.

================================================================================
libayatana-appindicator3
================================================================================
License: LGPL-3.0-only
Website: https://github.com/AyatanaIndicators/libayatana-appindicator
Source:  https://github.com/AyatanaIndicators/libayatana-appindicator
Full license: https://github.com/AyatanaIndicators/libayatana-appindicator/blob/master/COPYING

libayatana-appindicator3 provides the system tray icon functionality
using the StatusNotifierItem D-Bus protocol. It works on both X11 and
Wayland desktop environments.

================================================================================
json-glib
================================================================================
License: LGPL-2.1-or-later
Website: https://gnome.pages.gitlab.gnome.org/json-glib/
Source:  https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/json-glib
Full license: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/json-glib/-/blob/master/COPYING

json-glib is a GLib-based JSON parser/generator. shellkeep uses it for
reading and writing state files, recent connections, and JSONL history.

================================================================================
OpenSSL
================================================================================
License: Apache-2.0
Website: https://www.openssl.org/
Source:  https://github.com/openssl/openssl
Full license: https://github.com/openssl/openssl/blob/master/LICENSE.txt

OpenSSL >= 3.0 provides the cryptographic primitives used by libssh.
The Apache-2.0 license (used since OpenSSL 3.0) is compatible with
GPL-3.0-or-later.

Note: shellkeep does not link to OpenSSL directly; it is a transitive
dependency via libssh.

================================================================================
Pango (transitive via GTK 3)
================================================================================
License: LGPL-2.1-or-later
Website: https://pango.gnome.org/
Source:  https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/pango
Full license: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/pango/-/blob/main/COPYING

Pango is a text layout and rendering library, used transitively through
GTK 3 for rendering text in the UI. shellkeep does not link to Pango
directly.

================================================================================
Cairo (transitive via GTK 3)
================================================================================
License: LGPL-2.1-only OR MPL-1.1
Website: https://www.cairographics.org/
Source:  https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/cairo/cairo
Full license: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/cairo/cairo/-/blob/master/COPYING

Cairo is a 2D graphics library used by GTK 3 for rendering. shellkeep
does not link to Cairo directly; it is a transitive dependency via GTK.

================================================================================
GIO (part of GLib)
================================================================================
License: LGPL-2.1-or-later
Website: https://docs.gtk.org/gio/
Source:  https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/glib
Full license: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/glib/-/blob/main/COPYING

GIO provides high-level I/O, networking, and D-Bus support. It is part of
the GLib project and is used directly by shellkeep for asynchronous I/O
and file operations.

================================================================================
libsystemd (optional, runtime only)
================================================================================
License: LGPL-2.1-or-later
Website: https://systemd.io/
Source:  https://github.com/systemd/systemd
Full license: https://github.com/systemd/systemd/blob/main/LICENSE.LGPL2.1

libsystemd is an optional dependency used for systemd journal (journald)
logging integration. It is only linked when available and the journald
option is enabled at build time.

================================================================================
cmocka (development/testing only)
================================================================================
License: Apache-2.0
Website: https://cmocka.org/
Source:  https://git.cryptomilk.org/projects/cmocka.git
Full license: https://git.cryptomilk.org/projects/cmocka.git/tree/COPYING

cmocka is a unit testing framework for C. It is used only for running
tests and is not included in release builds or distributed packages.

================================================================================
tmux (server-side, not linked)
================================================================================
License: ISC
Website: https://github.com/tmux/tmux
Source:  https://github.com/tmux/tmux
Full license: https://github.com/tmux/tmux/blob/master/COPYING

tmux is a terminal multiplexer used on the remote server as the session
persistence backend. shellkeep interacts with tmux via SSH commands and
control mode. tmux is NOT linked into shellkeep and is NOT distributed
with it; it must be independently installed on the server.

